               <p>MR. 
               <persName id="t18190915-238-person2032">
                  RICHARD 
                  STONHEWER ILLINGWORTH
               <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2032" type="surname" value="STONHEWER ILLINGWORTH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2032" type="given" value="RICHARD"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2032" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a <rs id="t18190915-238-viclabel1282" type="occupation">wine-merchant</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190915-238-victim2031 t18190915-238-viclabel1282"></join>, and live in Waterloo-place, Pall Mall. On the 19th of July, about seven o'clock in the evening, I was passing through the narrow part of the <placeName id="t18190915-238-crimeloc1283">Strand, from Exeter Change</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t18190915-238-crimeloc1283" type="placeName" value="Strand, from Exeter Change"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t18190915-238-crimeloc1283" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18190915-238-off1280 t18190915-238-crimeloc1283"></join> to the other side, a person came up, and said my pocket had been picked. I felt, and missed my pocketbook - it contained several memorandums, two sovereigns, and four Portuguese gold coins. It was safe in my coat-pocket when I left my house. The prisoner was stopped, but I never found it.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. ADOLPHUS. Q. Had you been far - A. Only to Exeter Change.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-238-person2033">
                  JOSEPH 
                  ROBINS
               <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2033" type="surname" value="ROBINS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2033" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2033" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I live in Bedfordbury. I was in the Strand, and saw the prisoner catch hold of the prosecutor's coat with his left hand, and lift it up, then put his right hand into the left hand pocket, two others who were with him, at that instant closed upon him, and sheltered him from view. They kept following the prosecutor until he got to Southampton-street. One of them had a large bludgeon. I crossed to the other side of the way, they turned up Southampton-street. I informed Mr. Illingworth his pocket had been picked, and pointed to the prisoner, the prosecutor's son secured him - the others walked back into the Stand. I am sure I saw the prisoner's hand in the prosecutor's pocket.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18190915-238-person2034">
                  GEORGE 
                  ROBINSON
               <interp inst="t18190915-238-person2034" type="surname" value="ROBINSON"></interp>
